text: Gourie Cave is a large river cave in Manchester Parish in west-central Jamaica. At 3505 metres it is the longest cave known in the island. It is liable to flooding. ==See also== *List of caves#Jamaica *Jamaican Caves Organisation *Manchester Parish, Jamaica ==External links== *Aerial view. *Photos *Gourie Cave - Jamaican Caves Organisation ==References== Category:Caves of Jamaica Category:Geography of Manchester Parish Category:Caves of the Caribbean
